$PAR
True or false:
If a sequence of Riemann integrable functions \($LB f_n $RB\) defined on \([0,1]\)
is such that \(0 \leq f_n(x) \leq \frac{1}{n}\) for all \(x \in [0,1]\)
and all \(n \in \mathbb{N} ,\) then 
\(\lim\limits_{n\to \infty} \int_0^1 f_n = 0.\)
$BR
END_TEXT
