$PAR
True or false:
If a sequence of continuous functions \($LB f_n $RB\) defined on \([0,1]\)
converges uniformly to \(0\) and \(g \colon [0,1] \to \mathbb{R}\) is continuous, then
\(\lim\limits_{n\to \infty} \int_0^1 g(x)f_n(x)\, dx = 0.\)
$BR
